cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with road segmentation using neural networks, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network structure that combines convolutional and distributed LSTM layers, which involves deep learning techniques and could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem of road segmentation is also relevant to robotics, which could place the paper under cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper uses neural networks for processing, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
